lyricText: I’ve got no business praying and I’m finished being good, now I can finally be okay and not the way I thought I should.
All those empty rooms, we could have been anywhere, anywhere else. Instead, I made a bed with apathy
Isn't like I do this on purpose, I just forget the second I learned it
In another life, we were arsonists
And, baby, it came true, all the little things that I wished for, that I never said out loud, out of my mouth
The only heaven I'll be sent to is when I'm alone with you
Will you let me spend a lifetime trying? And if you do, I'll have time to write the book on you
